      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": ["PROMPT-GUIDED INPAINTING - FLUX.2 Klein 9B (companion to the Moebius examples)\n\nMoebius removes; it cannot follow instructions (no text encoder). When you want to PUT SOMETHING SPECIFIC in the hole ('replace the car with a fountain'), use this graph: a full generalist edit model with a real text encoder. ~10 GB of models vs Moebius' 1 GB, seconds instead of milliseconds - use Moebius when you just want things gone, this when you want to describe the replacement.\n\nHow to use: load an image, right-click -> Open in MaskEditor, paint the area to replace, write what should appear there in the positive prompt, Queue.\n\nMODELS (place in ComfyUI/models/...):\n- diffusion_models/flux-2-klein-9b-fp8.safetensors  (black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-base-9b-fp8 on HF, accept the license)\n- text_encoders/qwen_3_8b_fp8mixed.safetensors      (Comfy-Org/flux2-klein-9B on HF)\n- vae/flux2-vae.safetensors\n\nEXTRA NODE PACK: 'comfyui-inpaint-cropandstitch' (install via ComfyUI-Manager). The Inpaint Crop node cuts a 1024px context window around your mask so the model works at its native resolution, and Inpaint Stitch blends the result back into the full image.\n\nThe 4-step schedule + cfg 1 is the distilled Klein fast setting. ReferenceLatent feeds the full source image latent as edit context - that is what makes Klein blend the new content with the scene."],
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355",
      "title": "About this workflow"
    },
